I start only to stop minutes later and take a mental break because the words that come are much heavier than I anticipated, causing my resolve to buckle from their weight. So each time I stop, I try to create space between myself and the words by 1. breathing and 2. making some art, even if it's just a doodle or art journal page. Just now it was playing with selfies & filters while laying on the floor because that's where the 347 words I wrote 20 minutes ago put me. Going to take this as a cue to rest and not dive back into writing until Monday or Tuesday. cc: @eloranicole
